<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Cayetano
                                    Romero</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-31"><hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                    1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Foster</hi>: I received your little note
                            of this date, in reply to mine of the 28th of the closing month, in
                            which you acquaint me that you have infromed the Secretary of War of the
                            suggestion, which I took the liberty to make to you, of causing an
                            investigation that might explain the facts in regard to the detention of
                            Mexican soldiers at San Ignacio, Tex.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">C. Romero.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>